⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Extraordinary Man
node CRP · CRP · ⟦The Extraordinary Man:CRP:0cfb24⟧

WHO   — The Extraordinary Man — the article that licenses murder
WHAT  — The intellectual engine of the crime: the idea that history's ‘Napoleons’ are absolved by greatness, and that Raskolnikov might be one.
WHERE — CRP · Crime and Punishment  Framework inputs: Crime and Punishment (Dostoevsky, 1866)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the novel anatomises a specific modern poison — the self-flattering belief that exceptional minds are exempt from common morality.
HOW   — By a plausible article and a flattering self-application, turning a starving student into an executioner.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I whisper that you are above the rules that bind the herd — and I am the most seductive and murderous idea a clever, lonely man can hold.

